<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1931-03-31T12:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1931-03-31T12:00:00-05:00" n="823" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d823">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">817.48 Earthquake of 1931/10:
                            Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Chargé in Nicaragua</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Beaulac</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-03-31T12:00:00-05:00">March 31,
                                1931—noon</date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>24. Press reports announce serious earthquake.<note n="1" xml:id="d823fn1">The earthquake occurred a few minutes after 10
                                o’clock on the morning of March 31. See The American National Red
                                Cross, <hi rend="italic">Managua Earthquake: Official Report of the
                                    Relief Work in Nicaragua after the Earthquake of March 31,
                                    1931</hi> (Washington, 1931), p. 5.</note> Please report.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>